Naledi Shange, News24 ER24 (Picture: Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - A high profile government official and his driver were injured in an accident on the N12 near Fochville on Friday night, paramedics said.The government official was driving with a convoy which included several law enforcement vehicles when a truck allegedly veered into their lane, said ER24 spokesperson Werner Vermaak. "The driver of the SUV explained that he swerved in order to avoid a head on collision and the truck collided with the side of the SUV sending it off the road into a veld next to the road," Vermaak said.&nbsp;"The impact ripped one of the SUV's rear doors off."Both the government official and his driver escaped with moderate injuries.They were treated on scene before being transported to hospital.&nbsp;It is believed that the driver of the truck were questioned on the scene.It was not immediately clear what had led to the crash.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.